<node id="FINANCIAL INDICATORS">
  <data key="d0">METRIC</data>
  <data key="d1">Includes operating income, net profit, total assets, debt ratio, debt-to-assets ratio, return on equity, which reflect the company's financial performance and health.&lt;SEP&gt;Key metrics include operating income of $100 million, net profit of $20 million, total assets of $500 million, total liabilities of $200 million, shareholder equity of $300 million, cash flow of $50 million, debt ratio of 0.4, and return on equity of 6.67%&lt;SEP&gt;Operating income of $200 million reflects total business income within a certain period. Net profit of $50 million represents net income after costs and taxes. Total assets stand at $500 million, while total liabilities amount to $200 million. Shareholder equity reaches $300 million, with cash flow reported at $100 million.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d73178a270a56ecd4b5a838ae17c9002&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a13a1ab41c0cd055a4aea8f61c29426&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a62ff4f6b31d69fe0b86e45c1a16b1c2</data>
