</node>
<node id="SHAREHOLDER EQUITY">
  <data key="d0">EVENT</data>
  <data key="d1">Equity belonging to shareholders at the end of 2017, valued at $600 million.&lt;SEP&gt;Reached $300 million driven by net profit, dividend distributions, and capital reserves.&lt;SEP&gt;Refers to the total value of shares owned by shareholders, including paid-in capital and retained earnings.&lt;SEP&gt;Shareholder equity amounted to $1.5 billion.&lt;SEP&gt;Shareholder equity reached $400 million, driven by net profit and dividend distribution.&lt;SEP&gt;Shareholder equity represents the residual interest in the assets of a company after deducting liabilities.&lt;SEP&gt;Shareholder equity was $70 million in 2019, representing the amount of equity belonging to shareholders after accounting for net profit distribution and capital reserves.&lt;SEP&gt;The shareholder equity reached $350 million in 2021.&lt;SEP&gt;The shareholder equity stood at £5,500,000 in 2021, reflecting strong financial health post-debt restructuring.</data>
