</node>
<node id="ENTERTAINMENT ENTERPRISES INC">
  <data key="d0">ORGANIZATION</data>
  <data key="d1">Entertainment Enterprises Inc. is a company that embraces diversity and inclusion within the entertainment industry, actively engages in community programs, supports philanthropic causes aligned with its values, appoints new directors to enhance governance, involves shareholders in decision-making processes, responds promptly to fraud incidents while maintaining ethical standards, updates compliance practices to adhere to regulations, revises corporate governance policies for transparency and accountability, strengthens risk management measures, and appoints a new CEO to drive innovation.&lt;SEP&gt;Entertainment Enterprises Inc. is an entertainment company with reported total assets of $1.2 billion, total liabilities of $300 million, shareholder equity of $900 million, and a debt ratio of 25%. The company focuses on cost control measures and strategic capital operations for growth and profitability.</data>
